tewhatewha
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a long axe-like Maori weapon, usually of wood and having both blade and sharpened handle.


Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
