Edition:
Quote:  ... the <i>taiaha</i>, a kind of two-handed sword made of the hardest wood of the country; and the <i>tewhatewha,</i> a wooden battle-axe, having a sharp-pointed handle to enable it also to answer the purpose of a spear.
